This paper deals with bibliometrics, which is a subfield of information science and library science that involves the quantitative analysis of academic literature. The paper also uses machine learning techniques to classify researchers based on their bibliometric data. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with data analysis, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
